Pam Golding has launched its digital edition of Exquisite, its collection of some of the most prestigious properties in South Africa. According to the real estate specialist, the luxury property market is showing encouraging signs of growing activity, “and it is also at its most competitive pricing in over a decade”. Pam Golding said that it sells one in every three homes for in excess of R10 million. Also on its books are many beautiful homes for rent in numerous stunning locations including the Waterfront, Clifton, Camps Bay, and Fresnaye. Prices range between R55,000 and around R130,000 per month. One particular home stands head and shoulders above the rest – a 10 bedroom house in Constantia, priced at R330,000 per month. Tarrystone – Historical Home – is set on a well-manicured and secluded garden. Located just off Southern Cross Drive it comprises around two acres of land and has views over False Bay. Pam Golding said that double volumes / high ceilings and large reception rooms provide an element of space and offers sufficient accommodation with beautiful and separate guest cottages. State-of-the-art security (including a guardhouse), a manager’s office, two separate cottages for staff accommodation, private vineyards, a tennis court, fully equipped gym room, Jacuzzi, Koi pond and a sparkling swimming pool to top it off. Outside <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-452686" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Constantia-02.png" alt="" width="1303" height="863" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Constantia-02.png 1303w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Constantia-02-300x199.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Constantia-02-1024x678.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Constantia-02-768x509.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Constantia-02-1200x795.png 1200w" sizes="(max-widt